<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'bhakti_yoga.css' %>
<%= javascript_include_tag 'bhakti_yoga.js'%>

<div class='yoga-marg-container'>
  <div class='yoga-marg-section'>
    <div class='bhakti-yoga tantra-marg'>
      <div class='yoga-section-one'>
        <div>
          <div class='yoga-header'>
            <%= image_tag "grunge6.png", class: 'yoga-grunge-1'%>
            <div class='yoga-title'>
              Tantra Marg
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class='yoga-quate-section'>
            <%= image_tag "grunge2.png", class: 'yoga-grunge-2'%>
            <div class='yoga-quate'>
              The word “Tantra” literally means a technique or a technology. This is an inner technology. These are subjective methods not objective methods. But in the current understanding in society, the word "Tantra" refers to very unorthodox or socially unacceptable methods. It is just that certain aspects are used in a certain way. It is not any different from Yoga. It is a limb of Yoga called Tantra Yoga.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class='yoga-images'>
          <%= image_tag "shiva-shakti", class: 'yoga-image'%>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <%if admin_signed_in?%>
      <div class='buttons'>
        <%= link_to "Add-Item",  new_tantra_marg_path, class: 'add-item'%>
      </div>
    <%end%>
    <div class='bhakti-yogas-list'>
      <div class='yoga-section-two'>
        <%if @tantra_margs.present? %>
          <%= render partial: 'card', locals: { tantra_margs: @tantra_margs, total_records: @total_records} %>
        <%end%>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>